.SH "NAME"
gitty-config \- Configuration file format for gitty configuration files.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gitty/
.fi
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
If \f(CR$XDG_CONFIG_HOME\fP is either not set or empty, \f(CR$HOME/.config/\fP is used instead.
.SH "LIST"
.sp
Configuration file format a list of Git repos with tags.
.SS "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gitty/list.json
.fi
.br
.SS "LIST JSON SCHEMA"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[
   {
      "path" : <string>,
      "tags" : [ <string>, ... ]
   },
]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBpath\fP
.RS 4
Path to a Git repo.
.RE
.sp
\fBtags\fP
.RS 4
A list of tags for list filtering.
.RE
.SS "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.B Example repo list
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[
   {
      "path" : "/Users/someuser/Developer/DevNotes/",
      "tags" : [ "notes", "work" ]
   },
   {
      "path" : "/Users/someuser/Developer/Tinkering/",
      "tags" : [ "personal", "experimental" ]
   },
]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "ALIASES"
.sp
Configuration file format for a list of aliases.
.SS "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gitty/aliases.json5
.fi
.br
.SS "ALIASES JSON5 SCHEMA"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[
   {
      name\&    : <string>,
      args\&    : [ <string>, ... ],
      details : <string>,
      flags\&   : [ <string>, ... ],
      status\&  : [ <string>, ... ],
      delay\&   : <integer>,
      sort\&    : <string>
   },
   ...
]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBname\fP
.RS 4
Alias name.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
name : \*(Aqmyalias\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBargs\fP
.RS 4
Array of command arguments.
.sp
.B Command string only
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
args : [ \*(Aqgit status \-sb\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
.B Command string and positional arguments
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
args : [ \*(Aqecho "Hello $1"\*(Aq, \*(Aq_\*(Aq, \*(AqWorld\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
First element (required)
.RS 4
Command string. Single quotes are required to prevent shell from expanding variables like \f(CR$1\fP.
.RE
.sp
Second element (optional)
.RS 4
Zeroth argument (\f(CR$0\fP). Conventionally \f(CR_\fP or the name of the command.
.RE
.sp
Remaining elements (optional)
.RS 4
Positional arguments (\f(CR$1\fP, \f(CR$2\fP, etc.) passed to the command.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBdetails\fP
.RS 4
Description of an alias.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
details : \*(AqMy awesome alias to do stuff\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBflags\fP
.RS 4
Array of run subcommand flags.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
flags : [ \*(Aqquiet\*(Aq, \*(Aqparallel\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBcompact\fP, \fBparallel\fP, \fBquiet\fP
.RE
.sp
\fBstatus\fP
.RS 4
Array of run subcommand status logical expressions. To learn more about logical expressions see \fBgitty(1)\fP
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
status : [ \*(Aq!deleted & added\*(Aq, \*(Aqlocked\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBadded\fP, \fBclean\fP, \fBcopied\fP, \fBdeleted\fP, \fBdetached\fP, \fBignored\fP, \fBinitial\-commit\fP, \fBlocked\fP, \fBmodified\fP, \fBneeds\-pull\fP, \fBneeds\-push\fP, \fBneeds\-upstream\fP, \fBrenamed\fP, \fBsubmodule\fP, \fBsub\-commit\-change\fP, \fBsub\-modified\fP, \fBsub\-untracked\fP, \fBtype\-change\fP, \fBunmerged\fP, \fBuntracked\fP
.RE
.sp
\fBdelay\fP
.RS 4
Delay between sequential commands in milliseconds.
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
delay : 100
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBsort\fP
.RS 4
Sort the output.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
sort : \*(Aqunsorted\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBaz\fP, \fBza\fP, \fBunsorted\fP
.RE
.SS "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.B Aliases schema with \*(Aqfetch\*(Aq alias
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
[
   {
      name\&    : \*(Aqfetch\*(Aq,
      args\&    : [ \*(Aqgit fetch\*(Aq ],
      details : \*(AqFetch git changes\*(Aq,
      flags\&   : [ \*(Aqparallel\*(Aq, \*(Aqquiet\*(Aq ],
      status\&  : [],
      delay\&   : 0,
      sort\&    : \*(Aqaz\*(Aq
   },
]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "LAYOUT"
.sp
Configuration file format for layout.
.SS "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gitty/layouts/
.fi
.br
.SS "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
All layouts can be deleted or renamed except for the \fBbase\fP layout. If gitty can\(cqt find the \fBbase\fP layout, a new one will be generated.
.SS "LAYOUT JSON5 SCHEMA"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
{
   outputStyle\&    : <string>,
   executionMode\&  : <string>,
   countMode\&      : <string>,
   maxCount\&       : <integer>,
   maxCountStyle\&  : { <stylings> },
   aZSort\&         : <bool>,
   sortOrder\&      : [ <string>, ... ],
   truncationMode : <string>,
   components\&     : [ <components>, ... ],
   symbols\&        : {
      added\&         : <string>,
      clean\&         : <string>,
      copied\&        : <string>,
      deleted\&       : <string>,
      detached\&      : <string>,
      dirty\&         : <string>,
      ignored\&       : <string>,
      initialCommit : <string>,
      locked\&        : <string>,
      modified\&      : <string>,
      noUpstream\&    : <string>,
      pull\&          : <string>,
      push\&          : <string>,
      renamed\&       : <string>,
      separator\&     : <string>,
      stashes\&       : <string>,
      typeChange\&    : <string>,
      truncator\&     : <string>,
      unmerged\&      : <string>,
      untracked\&     : <string>,
      submodule\&     : {
         prefix\&       : <string>,
         commit\&       : <string>,
         modified\&     : <string>,
         untracked\&    : <string>,
         suffix\&       : <string>,
      },
   },
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fBoutputStyle\fP
.RS 4
Layout output style.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
outputStyle : \*(Aqcolumnar\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBcolumnar\fP, \fBlinear\fP
.RE
.sp
\fBexecutionMode\fP
.RS 4
Determines in what order to run status and custom components
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
executionMode : \*(Aqparallel\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES:
.sp
\fBparallel\fP \- run status in parallel alongside sequentially executed custom components
.br
\fBstatusThenCustom\fP \- run status then custom components sequentially
.br
\fBcustomThenStatus\fP \- run custom components sequentially then status
.sp
NOTE:
When any of the custom components uses \fBstatusInput\fP parameter, \fBexecutionMode\fP is switched to \fBstatusThenCustom\fP automatically.
.RE
.sp
\fBcountMode\fP
.RS 4
Count position for components with count.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
countMode : \*(Aqleading\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBleading\fP, \fBtrailing\fP
.RE
.sp
\fBmaxCount\fP
.RS 4
Maximum count number for components with count.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
maxCount : 99
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBmaxCountStyle\fP
.RS 4
Use styles and colors when count is exceeded \fBmaxCount\fP value.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
maxCountStyle : {
   fg : \*(Aqmagenta\*(Aq,
   bg : \*(Aqyellow\*(Aq,
   styles : [ \*(Aqunderline\*(Aq, \*(Aqbold\*(Aq ]
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: See \fBCOLORS & STYLES\fP section.
.RE
.sp
\fBaZSort\fP
.RS 4
Global sort direction for all components. Alphanumeric components (e.g. \fBrepo\fP, \fBhead\fP) sort A to Z. Presence\-based components (e.g. \fBmodified\fP, \fBadded\fP) sort from present to absent status.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
aZSort : true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBsortOrder\fP
.RS 4
Defines the sort precedence for status components. Components are evaluated from left to right, with earlier entries taking higher priority.
.sp
A \fB!\fP prefix negates the status, meaning the sort is based on the absence of that condition.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
sortOrder : [\*(Aqclean\*(Aq, \*(Aq!added\*(Aq, \*(Aqcustom: pwd\*(Aq, \*(Aqrepo\*(Aq]

In this example, components are sorted using the following rules, in order:

1. clean\&        sort repos from clean to dirty.
2. !added\&       sort repos without added files before repos with added files.
3. custom: pwd\&  sort alphanumerically by the output of the \*(Aqpwd\*(Aq custom component.
4. repo\&         sort alphanumerically by repo name.
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
  ASCENDING\&     | DESCENDING
 \-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
  custom: id\&    |
  head\&          |
  oid\&           |
  repo\&          |
  upstream\&      |
                |
  added\&         | !added
  clean\&         | !clean
  copied\&        | !copied
  deleted\&       | !deleted
  detached\&      | !detached
  ignored\&       | !ignored
  initialCommit | !initialCommit
  locked\&        | !locked
  modified\&      | !modified
  noUpstream\&    | !noUpstream
  pull\&          | !pull
  push\&          | !push
  renamed\&       | !renamed
  stashes\&       | !stashes
  submodules\&    | !submodules
  typeChange\&    | !typeChange
  unmerged\&      | !unmerged
  untracked\&     | !untracked
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fBtruncationMode\fP
.RS 4
Controls how dynamic component output is truncated when it exceeds the available width.
.sp
Applies to the following components: \fBcustom\fP, \fBhead\fP, \fBrepo\fP, \fBupstream\fP
.sp
Truncated output is shortened using the specified \fBtruncator\fP symbol.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
truncationMode : \*(Aqtail\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBhead\fP, \fBmiddle\fP, \fBtail\fP
.RE
.sp
\fBsymbols\fP
.RS 4
Select symbols for status components. All fields are required. (see \fBsymbols\fP in \fBLAYOUT JSON5 SCHEMA\fP)
.RE
.sp
\fBcomponents\fP
.RS 4
Select which components and in what order to show in the status. All component fields are optional except for the \fBcommand\fP field in \fBcustom\fP component.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
components : [
   { added\&  : {} },
   { custom : { command : \*(Aqpwd\*(Aq } },
]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Styling\-related fields like text style, foreground color, and background color are consolidated under \fI<stylings>\fP to avoid redundancy.
.sp
\fI<stylings>\fP
.RS 4
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
fg : <string>
bg : <string>
styles : [<string>, ...]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
USAGE:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
fg : \*(Aqmagenta\*(Aq
bg : \*(Aqyellow\*(Aq
styles : [ \*(Aqunderline\*(Aq, \*(Aqbold\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: See \fBCOLORS & STYLES\fP section.
.RE
.sp
\fBadded\fP
.RS 4
Shows that repo has added files.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
added : { <stylings> }
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fI<stylings>\fP
.RS 4
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBcleanOrDirty\fP
.RS 4
Shows whether repo is in clean or dirty state.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
cleanOrDirty : {
   showDirty\&   : <bool>,
   cleanFg\&     : <string>,
   cleanBg\&     : <string>,
   cleanStyles : [<string>, ...],
   dirtyFg\&     : <string>,
   dirtyBg\&     : <string>,
   dirtyStyles : [<string>, ...],
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
showDirty
.RS 4
Show \fBdirty\fP symbol when status is dirty, if \fBfalse\fP whitespace is used.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
showDirty : true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
cleanFg
.RS 4
Foreground color for \fBclean\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
cleanFg : \*(Aqred\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
cleanBg
.RS 4
Background color for \fBclean\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
cleanBg : \*(Aqext 130\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
cleanStyles
.RS 4
Text styles for \fBclean\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
cleanStyles : [ \*(Aqbold\*(Aq, \*(Aqunderline\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
dirtyFg
.RS 4
Foreground color for \fBdirty\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
dirtyFg : \*(Aqrgb 200 12 10\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
dirtyBg
.RS 4
Background color for \fBdirty\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
dirtyBg : \*(Aqhsb 300 0.3 0.8\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
dirtyStyles
.RS 4
Text styles for \fBdirty\fP symbol
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
dirtyStyles : [ \*(Aqfaint\*(Aq ]
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBcopied\fP
.RS 4
Shows that repo had copied files.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
copied : { <stylings> }
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fI<stylings>\fP
.RS 4
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBcustom\fP
.RS 4
Runs a custom command and renders its output as a component.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
custom : {
   command\&        : <string>,
   sortID\&         : <string>,
   statusInput\&    : <bool>,
   width\&          : <integer>,
   truncationMode : <string>,
   <stylings>
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
command
.RS 4
Command with arguments. Field is required.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
command : \*(Aqgit fetch\*(Aq,
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
To show default output when there is none use:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
command : \*(AqsomeCommand | grep . || echo "default output"\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
sortID
.RS 4
An identifier that uniquely names this component so it can be referenced in \fBsortOrder\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
sortID : \*(Aqfetch\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
statusInput
.RS 4
Pass status output to the custom component via standard input. This switches \fBexecutionMode\fP to \fBstatusThenCustom\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
statusInput : false
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Status output is expected to match the output of:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git status \-\-branch \-\-show\-stash \-\-porcelain=v2 \-\-ignored=no
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Or when \fBignored\fP component is used:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
git status \-\-branch \-\-show\-stash \-\-porcelain=v2 \-\-ignored=traditional
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
width
.RS 4
Column width.
.br
If specified, output will be truncated or expanded to the width.
.br
If not specified or set to \fBnull\fP, output will take as much space as it needs.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
width : 20
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
truncationMode
.RS 4
Truncation mode. Overrides global \fBtruncationMode\fP
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
truncationMode : \*(Aqtail\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
VALUES: \fBhead\fP, \fBmiddle\fP, \fBtail\fP
.RE
.sp
\fI<stylings>\fP
.RS 4
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBdeleted\fP
.RS 4
Shows that repo has removed files.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
deleted : { <stylings> }
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fI<stylings>\fP
.RS 4
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBdetached\fP
